<!DOCTYPE html>
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
      xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
      xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
      metal:use-macro="layout">
    <tal:block metal:fill-slot="main">
        <h1>
            Change Log
        </h1>
        <p>
            Ion Inspector is in a rolling deployment cycle like the Debian distribution of GNU/Linux, and in that fashion, changes to the site will roll out here as they go live on the site.
        </p>
        <dl>
            <dt>Q1 2013</dt>
            <dd>
                <ul>
                    <li>The archive report list view is paginated</li>
                    <li>A more compact, absolute/relative hybrid date time format is being used for the report list</li>
                    <li>The Version Check test indicates CSAs from old versions of the TS which should be upgraded</li>
                    <li>The Bead Loading test flags runs for which loading may be a concern.</li>
                </ul>
            </dd>
            <dt>Q4 2012</dt>
            <dd>
                <ul>
                    <li>Added a change log to the site which can be found <a href="/changes">here</a></li>
                    <li>Added an optional "Site Name" field to archive uploads.</li>
                    <li>Added "Re-run" which re-runs all tests on an archive as if it were freshly uploaded.</li>
                    <li>Added "Super delete" which deletes an archive, it's tests, all of their files from the system, as if it were never uploaded.</li>
                    <li>Fixed incompatibilities between TS 3.4 archives and the Filter Metrics and Separator Traces tests</li>
                    <li>For 3.4+ archives, Filter Metrics will report all Library read details contained in BaseCaller.json</li>
                    <li>Submitter and Site name autocompletion</li>
                    <li>Refined site layout by removing un-needed text and improving the upload form layout</li>
                    <li>Editing of archive meta data from check page</li>
                </ul>
            </dd>
        </dl>
    </tal:block>
</html>
